- Days Since Created: {{ $('Postgres: Get Active Leads').item.json.days_since_created }}
- Days Since Last Contact: {{ $('Postgres: Get Active Leads').item.json.days_since_contact }}

Re-scoring Factors:
1. Time decay: Leads get colder over time (reduce score by 5-10 points per week without contact)
2. Status progression: proposal_sent > qualified > contacted > new (no change for positive movement)
3. Urgency degradation: urgent leads become less urgent after 7+ days
4. Budget signal decay: high budget signals may decrease if no follow-up

Provide a new qualification score (0-100) and brief reasoning.

Respond ONLY in valid JSON format:
{
  "new_score": <number 0-100>,
  "score_change": <positive or negative number>,
  "reasoning": "<1-2 sentence explanation>",
  "recommendation": "<immediate_followup | schedule_followup | nurture | archive>",
  "urgency_adjusted": "<urgent | moderate | low>"
}",
  "stream": false
}

parameters.jsCode:
// Parse AI response
const aiResponse = JSON.parse($input.item.json.response);
const leadData = $('Postgres: Get Active Leads').item.json;
const originalScore = leadData.qualification_score;
const newScore = aiResponse.new_score;
const scoreChange = newScore - originalScore;

// Determine if this lead became "hot" (crossed 75 threshold)
const becameHot = originalScore < 75 && newScore >= 75;
const becameCold = originalScore >= 75 && newScore < 75;

return {
  json: {
    lead_id: leadData.id,
    email: leadData.email,
    name: `${leadData.first_name} ${leadData.last_name}`,
    company: leadData.company,
    original_score: originalScore,
    new_score: newScore,
    score_change: scoreChange,
    reasoning: aiResponse.reasoning,
    recommendation: aiResponse.recommendation,
    urgency_adjusted: aiResponse.urgency_adjusted,
    became_hot: becameHot,
    became_cold: becameCold,
    status: leadData.status,
    days_since_contact: leadData.days_since_contact
  }
};

